     <h2>Feature list and Roadmap</h2>
       <h3>Features</h3>
	<p>Here are the features currently implemented (0.1-CVS):</p>
	<ul>
	 <li>Deamons with partial job scheduling implemented</li>
	 <li>CLI interface to manage the databse of devices</li>
	 <li>Monitoring of devices' reachability through their http interfaces.</li>
	</ul>
       <h3>Roadmap</h3>
	<h4>1.0</h4>
	 <p>Here is the list of feature that we would like to achieve for the release of the version 1.0. This list is not exhaustive and may change over the time.</p>
	 <ul>
	  <li>Jobs Scheduling: Ability to schedule operations on devices like backuping config over the night, refreshing CMI database, cleaning logs, ...</li>
	  <li>Managing both pfsense and m0n0wall devices</li>
	  <li>E-mail notification based on criterias (device goes down, scheduled job failed, major change in the config of a device, ...)</li>
	  <li>Central syslog implemented inside CMI</li>
	  <li>Applying current rules to multiple devices</li>
	  <li>Grouping devices to allow operations on specific groups (i.e.: DMZ, LAN, WLAN, ...)</li>
	  <li>Overview of system's health (RRD graphs if possible)</li>
	 </ul>
